  "texts": [
    "In traditional actuarial work, AI can be utilised for tasks such as automation, predictive modelling, risk assessment, and optimisation of pricing and reserving strategies.",
    "Incorporating AI into traditional actuarial tasks has the potential to enhance the accuracy and efficiency of models and methods.",
    "For example, advanced ML techniques can be used to refine loss reserving estimates or improve the predictive power of underwriting models.",
    "By embracing AI technologies, actuaries can also better anticipate and respond to market trends, regulatory changes, and emerging risks.",
    "AI can also streamline various actuarial processes, such as massive data preparation, model validation, and reporting."
  ],
